26/02/2006
ROME, Italy -- Albanian President Alfred Moisiu held his first meeting with Pope Benedict XVI on Friday (24 February), within the framework of Moisiu's two-day official visit to Rome. They discussed Albania's Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU and other issues, including Kosovo. On Thursday evening, Moisiu met with Italian counterpart Carlo Azeglio Ciampi. Discussions focused on Rome's support for Albania's EU integration bid, as well as ways to boost co-operation in the tourism, industry, technology and service sectors. (Albanian News - 25/02/06; Albanian President Web site - 24/02/06)
